 cken in traffic\, to using dangerous construction sites as our playground
 \, childhood adventure was often intertwined with how far you were willin
 g to go--and the consequences that came with it. Armed with cherry bombs\
 , slingshots\, and more confidence than caution\, we pushed boundaries in
  ways that would make parents today shudder.
